SIMPLE: saltigrade
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saltigrade
<hw>Sal"ti*grade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>saltus</ets> a leap + <ets>gradi</ets> to walk, go: cf. F.
<ets>saltigrade</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having feet or
legs formed for leaping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saltigrade</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Saltigrade
<hw>Sal"ti*grade</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the
<fam>Saltigradae</fam>, a tribe of spiders which leap to seize their
prey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saltimbanco</ent>⟦br⟧
